      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — FDA centrifugal pump geometry",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.8M, fine 9.1M elements) performed on the FDA benchmark pump geometry at 2500 RPM, 5 L/min. Richardson extrapolation applied to velocity profiles at five cross-sections. Grid convergence index (GCI) < 2% for all monitored quantities on the fine mesh, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/morrison-mesh-gci",
        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Richardson extrapolation / GCI",
        "description": "GCI computed per Roache (1994) for velocity magnitude and wall shear stress at all monitored cross-sections. Maximum GCI 1.87% on fine mesh. Combined numerical uncertainty estimated at ±2.1% of peak shear stress.",
        "value": 0.021
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental validation — hemolysis index comparison against FDA PIV data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted velocity fields and derived hemolysis index (HI) values compared against FDA particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements for the generic centrifugal pump at five operating points (2000–3500 RPM, 3–6 L/min). Normalised RMS error in velocity magnitude < 8% across all operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed at all worst-case conditions. Validation activities span the full COU operating envelope.",
      "hasOutputComparison": {
