      "rationale": "Primary QoIs are the relative hemolysis index (RH) and peak scalar shear stress (SSmax). Both are directly used in the regulatory decision (RH < 1 acceptance criterion). Secondary QoIs (velocity profiles, pressure-flow curves) provide corroborating evidence of model fidelity."
